Durante e tempunan aya lat i e haltu Bieu Mitar, di Aristóteles enfoque di e investigashon riba e fenómeno natural a utilidat. Algun di e antiguo konosementu a bai pèrdí, òf na algun kasonan ta hala ta scur, durante di cai di Dominio Romani i korant di lucha polítika. Sinembargo, e komandante kampo di konosementu (òf di "filosofia natural"manera tabata yama) i un gran parti di e konosemento komandantenan di mundu bieu ta fortalesé su mes observa kla di e obranan di e promé latino encyclopedie manera con Isidoro di Sivil. Den e dominio Bintiun, hopi di e konosementu pagano text ta poní den Siríaco produccion hasí dor di grupo aki manera e Restorant i Manifesta.<ref name="history natural philosophy">{{Cite book|last=Grant|first=Edward|year=2007|title=A History of Natural Philosophy: From the Ancient World to the Nineteenth Century|pages=62–67|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-68957-1|ISBN=978-0-521-68957-1}}</ref> Hopi bon esakinan posteriormente tradusí e arabir bou di e Calypso, durante di kende hopi di e tipo clasico di prenda tin laga i den algun kasonan mehora.[./Science#cite_note-31 <span class="mw-reflink-text"><nowiki>[laar a apa 7]</nowiki></span>]{{efn|Alhacen had access to the optics books of Euclid and Ptolemy, as is shown by the title of his lost work ''A Book in which I have Summarized the Science of Optics from the Two Books of Euclid and Ptolemy, to which I have added the Notions of the First Discourse which is Missing from Ptolemy's Book'' From [[Ibn Abi Usaibia]]'s catalog, as cited in {{harv|Smith|2001}}{{rp|'''91'''(vol.1),p.xv}}}}

Di Kas di Sabiduria a kreá den Bosdi desaster di [[Bagdad|Bida]], [[Irak|Ik]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/place/Bayt-al-Hikmah|title=Bayt al-Hikmah|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Encyclopedia Brittanica|access-date=November 3, 2016}}</ref> e ta konsiderá komo un importante sentro intellectueel pa e Edat di Oro Islamita, kaminda e edits Baselmans manera den en Ind i Ibn Zal den Bida i bon Ibn den en Haha e Keiro flores di siglo ix na xxiii te di Mango saqueo di Bida. Ibn den en Haha, konosí mas biaha den Pabou manera un Almasen, momento e punto di bista Aristotélico<ref>{{cite journal|jstor=231249|last=Smith|first=A. Mark|date=December 1981|title=Getting the Big Picture in Perspectivist Optics|journal=Isis|volume=72|number=4|pages=568–589|doi=10.1086/352843}}</ref> , hasiendo hincapié na dat experiences.[./Science#cite_note-34 <span class="mw-reflink-text"><nowiki>[laar a apa 8]</nowiki></span>]{{efn|"[Ibn al-Haytham] followed Ptolemy's bridge building ... into a grand synthesis of light and vision. Part of his effort consisted in devising ranges of experiments, of a kind probed before but now undertaken on larger scale."— {{harvnb|Cohen|2010|p=59}}}}<ref>{{Cite book|year=2009|title=Oxford Dictionary of the Middle Ages|chapter=Science in Islam}}</ref>

Na e atardi di desaster media, manera e deseo di produccion bira grandi (por ehèmpel, di e Skol Produktor di Tolo), e Europe oksidente a kuminsá regular text skirbí no solamente na latin, e latino produccion di griego, arabir i hebreo. Den partikular, e text di Aristóteles, Ptolomeo,[./Science#cite_note-36 <span class="mw-reflink-text"><nowiki>[laar a apa 9]</nowiki></span>]{{efn|The translator, [[Gerard of Cremona]] (c. 1114–87), inspired by his love of the [[Almagest]], came to Toledo, where he knew he could find the Almagest in Arabic. There he found Arabic books of every description, and learned Arabic in order to translate these books into Latin, being aware of 'the poverty of the Latins'.&nbsp;—As cited by Charles Burnett (2001) "The Coherence of the Arabic-Latin Translation Program in Toledo in the Twelfth Century", pp. 250, 255, & 257, ''Science in Context'' '''14'''(1/2), 249–288 (2001). DOI: 10.1017/0269889701000096}} i di Eclips, ku ta preservá den e Kasnan di e Sabiduria, e buska entre edits Katóliko. Den Oropa, e produccion latin di e Almasen di ''Buki Tica'' korektamente influensia Roep Con (siglo 13), Inglatera, kende bog pa mas konosementu experimenta manera e ta demostrá pa Almasen. Na e lat di e Bieu Mitar, un síntesis di Catolicismo i e vishon aristotélica konosí komo e Scolastica a florin den Oropa pabou, nan a bira un nobo sentro geográfiko di konosementu, sino tur e aspekto di scolastica tabata critico na semper 15 i 16.

